  {"a":"jinx_bot","b":"kogmaw","win":["Jinx","Jinx","Jinx","Jinx","Skill","Jinx","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You own this window. Kog'Maw is a slow, immobile hyper-carry with no escape, and before his Bio-Arcane Barrage (W) attack-range steroid is meaningful your minigun range and Q rockets let you poke and push him around freely. Set up your support for an all-in: he can't dodge Flame Chompers! and has no dash, so any CC catches him. Shove the wave and deny him safe farm."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Roughly even at 6. Kog's ultimate Living Artillery (R) gives him long-range poke to zone you off farm, but it doesn't save him from a commit, and your own R (Super Mega Death Rocket!) plus support CC still threatens to delete him. Keep pressuring his lack of mobility, dodge his artillery lobs, and look for the all-in when his W or positioning is bad."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Back to Jinx at one item. Your first crit spike plus Excite steroid keeps you ahead of Kog's own item timing, and because he's the most immobile carry in the game your all-in threat with E and support CC only grows. Punish him under his own tower, deny farm, and force him to play from behind while you snowball the wave."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late is a genuine skill matchup and the reason this lane is close: Kog'Maw with a completed W and on-hit items out-DPSes almost everyone at his effective range, so if he's allowed to free-fire in a teamfight he can beat your minigun. It comes down to positioning and peel: you must space so his backline artillery and short-range shred can't reach you, blow him up with R or a flank before he ramps, and not let a protected Kog auto your team down."}],"wants":{"you":["The early-to-mid window where you punish his immobility before W ramps","All-ins with support CC and Flame Chompers! on an escape-less target","First-item crit spike to stay ahead of his own item timing"],"foe":["Reaching a completed W and on-hit items to out-DPS you at range late","Living Artillery poke to zone you off farm and chip you down","A peel-heavy team that lets him free-fire safely in teamfights"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are firmly Jinx-favoured. Kog'Maw is slow, immobile, and has no escape, and before his W range steroid matters your minigun and Q rockets out-poke and out-push him. Shove the wave, deny his farm, and set up all-ins, since Flame Chompers! and any support CC land freely on a target that can't dash away.","mid":"Levels 5-6 are roughly even. Kog's Living Artillery gives him long-range poke to contest your zone, but it doesn't rescue him from a commit and your own ult plus support CC still threatens to delete him. Dodge his artillery lobs, keep punishing his immobility, and look for the all-in whenever his positioning slips.","late":"Late is a true skill matchup and why the win rate is close. A fully online Kog'Maw with completed W and on-hit shred out-DPSes you at his effective range if he's allowed to free-fire, so the game hinges on positioning: space beyond his reach, blow him up with Super Mega Death Rocket! or a flank before he ramps, and never let a peeled Kog auto your team down.","whys":["Level 1 favours Jinx: you out-range and push an immobile Kog before his W matters.","Level 2 stays Jinx's as your poke and all-in threat grow on an escape-less target.","Level 3 favours Jinx with support CC and Flame Chompers! landing freely on him.","Level 4 remains Jinx's window as you deny farm and pressure his immobility.","Level 5-6 evens out as Living Artillery gives Kog long-range poke to contest your zone.","At first item Jinx's crit spike keeps you ahead of Kog's own timing.","Late is a skill matchup: a free-firing Kog can out-DPS you, so positioning decides it."]},
  {"a":"jinx_bot","b":"lucian","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Jinx","Jinx","Jinx"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Lucian owns the early game: his double-tap Q, dash-cancel autos with Passive, and E-into-Piltover Peacemaker let him win every short trade, so respect his aggression and only walk up when his E dash is down."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Super Mega Death Rocket flips the lane; you outscale Lucian's Culling and can chunk him from screen-range if he overextends looking for a kill on a low support."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once you finish first item you spin up Pow-Pow rockets and Fishbones minigun range, giving you waveclear, tower siege, and DPS that a lane-bully Lucian falls off against."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game is a landslide for you: Get Excited! resets, rocket splash, and rockets that outrange Lucian mean you delete him before Culling ever reaches its second dash."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach 2-3 completed items where Fishbones range and Get Excited! resets take over","Fights where your support peels Lucian's E dash so you free-fire rockets","A farm-focused early where you concede kills but never fall behind on CS"],"foe":["A snowball level 2-3 all-in with his support before your rockets scale","Short trades where his Passive double-auto and Q punish your minigun walk-ups","To end the game before your item count and range make him irrelevant"]},"early":"Lucian outbullies you at levels 1-3: his Lightslinger passive turns every ability into two hits, and Q plus E lets him dash-trade and reset instantly, so keep Pow-Pow on and last-hit from behind your minions rather than contesting minigun trades you'll lose.","mid":"Around level 6 the lane balances and tips your way; your Super Mega Death Rocket punishes any Lucian overextension from max range, and while he still wants short all-ins with E up, you can now match his damage and threaten the execute if he dives.","late":"After your first item and beyond this is heavily your matchup: Fishbones outranges everything Lucian has, rocket splash clears waves and sieges, and Get Excited! resets in fights let you snowball where Lucian's early-game power has fully expired.","whys":["Level 1 is even because neither of you has the tools to commit a hard trade with only one ability rank.","Level 2 stays a skill check as Lucian's second point enables early aggression but you can position safely behind minions.","Level 3 is close, decided by whether Lucian lands his E-Q combo or you dodge and farm cleanly.","Levels 4-5 remain even; Lucian's kill pressure is real but you can trade back with minigun stacks and disengage.","Level 6 favors you because Super Mega Death Rocket adds screen-range pickoff and execute pressure Lucian can't answer.","First item favors you as rocket range, splash, and Get Excited! resets outscale Lucian's lane-bully spike.","With two-plus items you dominate: your range and DPS render Lucian's short-range burst obsolete in every fight."]},
  {"a":"jinx_bot","b":"missfortune","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Miss Fortune","Miss Fortune","Jinx"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Miss Fortune's Double Up bounces off minions to hit you for burst plus her passive Love Tap, so avoid standing directly behind low-health minions and don't let her free-poke you off the wave."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Bullet Time is a game-ending zone in the 2v2; if her support lands CC she can channel Strut-fueled Make It Rain plus ult and delete you, so hold Flash and never fight in a chokepoint."},{"when":"1st item","text":"MF's first-item power with lethality and her ult make her the stronger all-in threat; group only with vision and never get caught facing an unflanked Bullet Time."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game swings back to you: your Fishbones range and Get Excited! resets outscale her once teams spread out and her stationary channel is easy to interrupt or sidestep."}],"wants":{"you":["Spread teamfights where MF can't line up a multi-target Bullet Time","Reaching 3+ items so your minigun DPS and rocket resets take over","Cleansing or bursting her before she finishes the ult channel"],"foe":["A grouped, choked fight where Bullet Time hits your whole team","Lethality first-item spikes to burst you with Double Up and Make It Rain","An all-in with support CC that locks you for the full ult"]},"early":"The early lane is a skill matchup: MF's Double Up rewards her if you stand behind low minions, but her mana and Strut-reliant mobility mean she can't chase you if you punish her Q on cooldown, so trade back when she steps up and last-hit patiently.","mid":"From level 6 MF holds the edge because Bullet Time is a devastating 2v2 tool; if her support engages you're forced to Flash or eat massive damage, so play around vision, respect chokepoints, and don't group into an unflanked channel.","late":"Once you hit two-plus items the matchup returns to you: your Fishbones outranges her, rocket splash and Get Excited! resets snowball spread fights, and her stationary ult becomes a liability you can walk out of or blow up before it finishes.","whys":["Level 1 is even as neither champion has a committing tool with a single ability rank.","Level 2 is a skill check decided by minion positioning and whether MF lands Double Up cleanly.","Level 3 stays even; her Q poke is real but her mana costs limit sustained aggression.","Levels 4-5 remain a skill matchup as you can trade back and disengage from her Strut walk-ups.","Level 6 favors Miss Fortune because Bullet Time is a fight-ending 2v2 ult that dwarfs your single rocket.","First item favors MF as lethality plus her ult make her the stronger all-in and pick threat.","With two-plus items you reclaim the matchup: range, resets, and spread fights nullify her channeled ult."]},
  {"a":"jinx_bot","b":"nilah","win":["Jinx","Nilah","Nilah","Skill","Nilah","Nilah","Jinx"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Nilah is a melee lane bully once she has Q range extension and E dashes; she'll close on you and burst with her shared-heal aggression, so keep Fishbones range up and kite backward the instant she dashes in."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Apotheosis is a huge 2v2 all-in: it pulls, disarms, and heals her whole side, so if her support engages you get locked and disarmed while she cleaves you down; hold Flash for it."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With her first crit item Nilah's cleave, sustain, and dash-reset E make her the stronger dueler; never let her get on top of you without support peel."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game flips back to you: if your team peels her E dashes you free-cast Fishbones and Get Excited! resets from range where her melee reach can never touch you."}],"wants":{"you":["Level 1 poke before her Q range and dashes come online","Peel that stops her E from dashing onto you, then kite at max range","Late fights where your Fishbones range keeps her melee cleave off you"],"foe":["Levels 2-6 where her Q, E dashes, and Apotheosis let her stick to you","A support all-in so her disarm ult locks you during her burst","First-item duels where her cleave and self-heal outtrade you"]},"early":"You actually win level 1: Nilah is melee with no range or dash yet, so use Pow-Pow autos and rocket poke to chunk her before she can retaliate and start the lane ahead.","mid":"From level 2 through 6 Nilah takes over as a lane bully; her extended Q reach, her E dash that resets on kills, and her shared sustain let her dive and outtrade you, and Apotheosis at 6 gives her a disarm-and-heal all-in you must respect with Flash and support peel.","late":"After first item she remains the stronger dueler up close, but as the game goes long the matchup returns to you: with two-plus items and a peel support you kite her melee dashes and free-fire Fishbones, and Get Excited! resets let you snowball fights she can't reach.","whys":["Level 1 favors you because Nilah is melee with no range or dash and eats your autos and rockets for free.","Level 2 favors Nilah as her Q range extension and first E dash let her close and trade onto you.","Level 3 favors Nilah; full dash access and sustain make her a sticky lane bully you can't easily kite.","Levels 4-5 are even as your extra rocket damage lets you trade back if you avoid her dash windows.","Level 6 favors Nilah because Apotheosis is a disarm, pull, and team-heal all-in that beats your single rocket.","First item favors Nilah as crit cleave and self-heal make her the dominant close-range dueler.","With two-plus items you reclaim the lane: range and resets keep her melee cleave off you in every fight."]},
  {"a":"jinx_bot","b":"samira","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Samira","Samira","Jinx"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Samira wants to build her combo style meter by mixing her W-blocked projectiles and E dash into you; keep your distance and don't feed her Q slashes, and use Pow-Pow autos to poke her when her E is on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Inferno Trigger is a lifesteal-fueled 2v2 execute; if her support lands knock-up CC she can dash in, ult, and delete your whole backline, so never fight in melee range of an engage support."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Samira spikes hard on her first crit item with E-reset aggression and W blocking your rockets, making her the stronger all-in threat; deny her the reset by not dying and never dash range."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game is firmly yours: your Fishbones outrange her dash, and if your team peels her E and stops her ult reset, you kite and delete her from range where her all-in never lands."}],"wants":{"you":["Kiting at Fishbones range where her E dash can't reach a reset","Peel and CC that interrupt her Inferno Trigger channel","Reaching 3+ items so your range and DPS bury her all-in window"],"foe":["Melee-range fights where she chains E resets and blocks rockets with W","A support knock-up to guarantee her Inferno Trigger execute","First-item crit spikes to snowball off style-meter aggression"]},"early":"The early lane is a skill matchup: Samira has to get in range to build her style meter, and her W can windwall your rockets, so poke her with autos when her E dash is down and never give her a free target to slash with Q into E.","mid":"From level 6 Samira holds the edge because Inferno Trigger plus her lifesteal makes her a terrifying 2v2 all-in; if her support engages with any knock-up she dashes in and executes, so respect her dive range, hold Flash, and don't clump in melee.","late":"By two-plus items the matchup swings hard to you: your Fishbones outrange every tool she has, and with a support peeling her E dashes and interrupting the ult, you free-fire from range and use Get Excited! resets to snowball where her all-in can never reach you.","whys":["Level 1 is even as neither champion can commit a hard trade with one ability rank.","Level 2 stays a skill check; Samira wants to build style meter but you can poke and disengage.","Level 3 remains even, decided by whether she lands her E dash into your line or you kite it.","Levels 4-5 are a skill matchup as your rockets trade back when her dash is down.","Level 6 favors Samira because Inferno Trigger is a lifesteal execute all-in that beats your single rocket.","First item favors Samira as crit and E resets make her the dominant close-range all-in threat.","With two-plus items you take over: Fishbones range and resets keep her dash-reset combo off you entirely."]},
  {"a":"jinx_bot","b":"senna","win":["Senna","Senna","Senna","Senna","Senna","Jinx","Jinx"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Senna outranges you with Piercing Darkness and her long autos, and she farms souls to stack range and crit; respect her Q poke, don't stand in the line behind minions she can pierce, and last-hit carefully under her range advantage."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Dawning Shadow gives Senna a global shield-or-execute and her Curse of the Black Mist camouflage engage, so she can support-carry the 2v2 while you're still scaling; play safe and farm."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Senna's first-item soul stacking still keeps her ahead on range and utility; don't force fights into her Q poke, and wait for your minigun and rockets to come fully online."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game is yours: once you have Fishbones range and Get Excited! resets, your raw DPS and rocket splash far exceed Senna's, whose damage is spread into utility and whose short-range moments you punish."}],"wants":{"you":["Farming safely to two-plus items where your DPS eclipses hers","Fights where Senna is forced to auto in your Fishbones range","Get Excited! reset snowballs once your rockets outrange her poke"],"foe":["The long early game where her Q range and soul stacks poke you down","Level 6 global ult plays and camouflage engages while you scale","Keeping the game slow and poke-based so your item spike never lands"]},"early":"Senna dominates the early lane: her Piercing Darkness heals her side and pokes you, her autos outrange yours, and she farms souls that stack permanent range and crit, so you're forced to last-hit cautiously and eat poke rather than trade back.","mid":"Through level 6 Senna stays ahead because her Dawning Shadow is a global shield-or-execute and her camouflage lets her roam and engage, letting her out-influence the map while your minigun and rockets are still ramping; just farm safely and avoid her Q lines.","late":"After your first item and especially with two-plus items the matchup flips fully to you: your Fishbones outrange her, your minigun and rocket splash out-DPS her utility-focused kit, and Get Excited! resets let you snowball teamfights where Senna's damage falls short.","whys":["Level 1 favors Senna because her longer autos and Q range let her poke you for free.","Level 2 favors Senna as her Q heal-poke and soul stacks build an early lead over you.","Level 3 favors Senna; her range and sustain keep you pinned while she farms souls.","Levels 4-5 favor Senna as her stacking range advantage grows and she out-pokes your walk-ups.","Level 6 favors Senna because her global ult and camouflage engage out-influence the 2v2 while you scale.","First item favors you as your minigun and rockets come online and start out-DPSing her utility kit.","With two-plus items you take over decisively: Fishbones range and resets bury Senna's spread damage."]},
  {"a":"jinx_bot","b":"seraphine","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Seraphine","Seraphine","Jinx","Jinx"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Seraphine as an APC pokes with her Q and slows with E, chunking you through minions; sidestep her E so she can't follow with an empowered Q, and don't sit in her poke while last-hitting."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Encore is a long-range chained root that sets up her support's all-in; if it lands on you in the 2v2 you get chained and bursted, so hold Flash and don't group into a line-up for her ult."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Seraphine's first AP item spikes her poke and shield sustain, keeping her ahead in the harass war; play around her E cooldown and wait for your own scaling to arrive."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game is yours: your Fishbones range and Get Excited! resets out-DPS her, and if you dodge or Flash the Encore root her poke-based kit can't stop your minigun from shredding her team."}],"wants":{"you":["Reaching two-plus items where your DPS outscales her poke","Sidestepping E and Encore so her root chains never connect","Get Excited! reset fights once your rockets outrange her harass"],"foe":["The mid-lane poke phase where Q and E slow-chunk you down","Level 6 Encore roots that chain into her support's all-in","First-item AP spikes to win the sustained harass war"]},"early":"The early lane is a skill matchup: Seraphine's Q out-pokes you and her E slow can set up a follow-up, but her mana is limited and she's squishy, so dodge her E, punish her when abilities are down, and farm without eating free harass.","mid":"From level 4 into 6 Seraphine takes the edge; her Q-E poke chunks you and her Encore is a long-range chained root that lets her support all-in you, so respect her ult range, sidestep her line abilities, and don't clump for the double-root setup.","late":"After first item and with two-plus items the matchup swings to you: your Fishbones outrange her poke, your minigun and rocket splash out-DPS her, and as long as you dodge or Flash the Encore root, Get Excited! resets let you snowball fights where Seraphine simply can't peel your damage.","whys":["Level 1 is even as neither champion threatens a committing trade at one rank.","Level 2 stays a skill check; her Q pokes but her mana and squishiness limit sustained aggression.","Level 3 remains even, decided by whether her E slow connects into a Q or you sidestep it.","Levels 4-5 favor Seraphine as her Q-E poke combo chunks you through the minion wave.","Level 6 favors Seraphine because Encore is a long-range chained root that enables her support's all-in.","First item favors you as your minigun and rockets come online and out-DPS her poke kit.","With two-plus items you take over: Fishbones range and resets outscale her harass and utility."]},
  {"a":"jinx_bot","b":"sivir","win":["Sivir","Sivir","Sivir","Skill","Sivir","Jinx","Jinx"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Sivir owns this window: her Q (Boomerang Blade) plus W (Ricochet) shove the wave into your tower and poke you off CS, and her Spell Shield eats your best engage tool by blocking a bomb or a support hook. On Pow-Pow miniguns you have no range answer to Q poke, so play behind the caster minions and just farm rather than contest a losing trade."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Still Sivir-favoured. Your Super Mega Death Rocket is a strong pick tool, but On The Hunt (her R) gives her team a movement-speed steroid to dodge your rockets and disengage or chase, blunting your 6 spike. Only fire Rockets when she has burned R or is body-blocked, and respect that her wave-clear lets her roam or reset on tempo."},{"when":"1st item","text":"The matchup flips here. Once you finish your first crit or attack-speed item and start swapping to Fishbones, your rockets outrange Sivir's Q entirely and each takedown resets you into permanent Get Excited! attack speed and move speed. Farm safely to your item timer, then start poking her out of lane with Fishbones from max range."},{"when":"Late","text":"With 2+ items you are the far superior teamfighter. Fishbones bounce splash melts her grouped-up team while Pow-Pow attack speed shreds her once Spell Shield is popped. Sit at the very back behind your frontline, let a support or bruiser force her Shield, and cash out on the reset chain to take over the fight."}],"wants":{"you":["First-item timer where Fishbones outranges her Q poke","A support who can bait or CC through her Spell Shield","Grouped 5v5s where Fishbones splash and Get Excited! resets snowball"],"foe":["A short lane where her Q+W poke chunks you every wave","Your engage tools wasted into her Spell Shield","Picking off your team before you complete items so you never spike"]},"early":"Sivir dominates levels 1-3: Boomerang Blade and Ricochet out-range and out-push you while Spell Shield neutralizes your engage, so give ground, farm under tower, and don't walk up to trade.","mid":"Through level 6 you're still behind because On The Hunt lets her dodge your Rockets and control tempo; play for CS, dodge Q, and save Rockets for when her Shield or R is down.","late":"From your first item onward Fishbones outranges everything she has and every kill resets Get Excited!, so poke her out and stomp the 2+ item teamfights from max range.","whys":["Level 1 is Sivir's: Boomerang Blade poke and superior push let her control the wave and chip you immediately.","Level 2 stays Sivir-favoured as W Ricochet adds wave pressure and pokes you off the caster minions.","Level 3 Sivir is ahead with her full poke-and-shove kit plus Spell Shield shutting down your engage.","Levels 4-5 are even skill: you can farm safely under tower while she pushes, so trades come down to positioning and Shield usage.","Level 6 tilts to Sivir because On The Hunt's speed lets her dodge Super Mega Death Rocket and dictate the tempo.","First item is Jinx's: Fishbones now outranges her Q and each takedown resets your Get Excited! steroid.","With 2+ items Jinx wins on Fishbones splash and reset-fueled attack speed in grouped teamfights."]},
  {"a":"jinx_bot","b":"smolder","win":["Jinx","Jinx","Jinx","Jinx","Skill","Jinx","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You dominate the early game. Smolder is a stacking scaling champ who is weak and low-range until his Q (Super Scorcher Breath) racks up stacks, so bully him now: swap to Fishbones and use the AoE bounce to poke him off CS and deny stacks. On Pow-Pow you win extended trades because he has no reliable disengage before items, and every last-hit you deny slows his entire game plan."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Even-ish here. Smolder's R (Mobile Wildfire) is a mobility-and-damage ult that lets him reposition or dodge your Rockets, offsetting your own level 6. Your Super Mega Death Rocket still snipes him if he's stack-farming greedily, so keep punishing, but respect that his ult gives him an escape you didn't have to worry about at level 3."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You spike hard again. Your first crit/attack-speed item lands well before Smolder's stack payoff, so this is your kill window: force all-ins with your support, chase with Get Excited! move speed, and end the lane before he hits 125 stacks. Every plate and kill you take here is tempo he can't get back."},{"when":"Late","text":"Skill/even. This is Smolder's payoff zone: fully stacked, his Q becomes a long-range nuke and his W (Achooo!) plus dragon-fed damage rival your DPS. You still out-teamfight him with Fishbones splash and resets, but you must close the game on your item lead rather than let him free-scale into a monster."}],"wants":{"you":["An aggressive early lane that denies Smolder his Q stacks","A support with CC to convert your level 3-5 kill pressure","Ending the game on your item spike before he fully stacks"],"foe":["A safe, farm-heavy lane where he freely stacks Q","His R to escape your all-ins and Rockets","A long game where fully-stacked Q outranges your Fishbones"]},"early":"You own levels 1-4: Smolder is a weak stacking champ pre-items, so use Fishbones AoE to deny his Q stacks and win any extended Pow-Pow trade.","mid":"Level 6 evens out because Mobile Wildfire gives him an escape from your Rockets, but your first item flips it back and this is your prime all-in window before he scales.","late":"Once he's fully stacked his Q nuke and dragon damage rival yours, so the game is even; you still win teamfights on splash and resets but must close before he free-scales.","whys":["Level 1 is Jinx's: Smolder is a low-range stacking champ with nothing to punish your Fishbones poke.","Level 2 stays yours as you deny his early Q stacks and pressure him off CS.","Level 3 Jinx wins extended trades since Smolder has no disengage before items.","Levels 4-5 remain Jinx-favoured because he's still under-stacked and vulnerable to your all-ins.","Level 6 is even: Mobile Wildfire gives Smolder a reposition/escape that offsets your Rocket spike.","First item is Jinx's: your crit spike lands well before his stack payoff, opening a hard kill window.","With 2+ items it's even skill as fully-stacked Smolder's Q nuke and scaling rival your DPS."]},
  {"a":"jinx_bot","b":"swain","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Swain","Jinx","Skill","Jinx"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is Swain's grab window. His E (Nevermove) roots you and his W plus Q let a bot-lane Swain nuke you if you're pulled, and once he lands E into his support's follow-up you can get bursted. Stay behind your minions so his E lands on creeps, farm with Fishbones from range, and don't give him a straight-line root angle."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"You're favoured at 6. Swain's Demonic Ascension (R) is a sustained-damage teamfight steroid, not a duel-winner in a spaced 2v2, and your Super Mega Death Rocket plus Pow-Pow burst can drop him before he generates enough Soul Fragments to heal through it. Kite backward, dodge his E, and punish when he ults into a fight he can't lock you down in."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Even/skill. Swain's first item (usually Liandry's/Blackfire) makes his DoT and R-heal much stickier, offsetting your own crit spike. You still out-DPS him on raw auto damage, but he becomes hard to kill through the sustain, so treat this as a farm-and-poke phase rather than a hard all-in window."},{"when":"Late","text":"You take over with 2+ items. Swain is a mid-game teamfight threat but falls off as a pure damage carry, while your Fishbones splash and Get Excited! resets scale into the best late-game DPS. Position at max range behind your frontline so his E and R never catch you, and shred his grouped team from safety."}],"wants":{"you":["Spaced trades where Swain's E roots minions, not you","Level 6 fights where you burst him before his R sustains","Late 2+ item teamfights where Fishbones and resets outscale him"],"foe":["A straight-line angle to land E (Nevermove) into a follow-up","Extended engages where Demonic Ascension heals him up","First-item DoT sustain making him unkillable in lane"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are even skill: neither of you wins outright, so respect Swain's E root angle, farm behind minions, and trade only when his E is down.","mid":"Level 4-5 tilts to Swain as his E-into-burst combo comes online, but level 6 flips to you because you can Rocket-and-kite him down before Demonic Ascension out-sustains your burst.","late":"His first item sustain evens the fight, but from 2+ items you're the superior scaling carry, poking his grouped team with Fishbones from max range while dodging E.","whys":["Level 1 is even skill with no strong lever for either side on the opening wave.","Level 2 stays even as both scale toward their real power without a decisive tool.","Level 3 remains skill-based: it hinges on whether Swain can land E, which you can dodge behind minions.","Levels 4-5 are Swain's: his Nevermove root into W/Q burst is his main kill window.","Level 6 is Jinx's: you burst and kite him before Demonic Ascension's sustain wins an extended fight.","First item is even skill as Swain's DoT-and-heal itemization offsets your crit spike.","With 2+ items Jinx wins on superior scaling, Fishbones splash, and safe max-range positioning."]},
  {"a":"jinx_bot","b":"tristana","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Tristana","Tristana","Jinx"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Roughly even, played on the wave. Tristana's passive gives her scaling auto range and her W (Rocket Jump) is both mobility and an escape, but she's an all-in champ with no poke, so neither of you wins a straight farm phase. Use Fishbones to deny her CS and keep the wave in a spot where her W-in isn't a free reset-detonation on you; if she jumps, punish the cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Tristana-favoured. Her R (Buster Shot) is a burst-and-knockback finisher that pairs with her E (Explosive Charge) detonation to blow you up in one all-in combo, and it doubles as a disengage from your Rockets. Don't overstay at low HP within her W range, and respect that her level 6 all-in with support CC can kill you through your own escape."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Still Tristana's window. Once she completes her first attack-speed/crit item her W reset (on takedown) and E charge stacking make her all-in damage spike hard, and she can dive you under tower with her jump. Play safe, freeze or hold the wave away from her tower, and don't give her a reset-fueled dive; your own spike hasn't fully overtaken hers yet."},{"when":"Late","text":"You reclaim the matchup at 2+ items. Tristana's power is front-loaded around her all-in, while your Fishbones splash, uncapped auto range on Pow-Pow, and Get Excited! resets make you the superior sustained-DPS teamfighter. Space so her W-in commitment lands into your frontline, kite her jump backward, and out-range her in grouped fights."}],"wants":{"you":["Late 2+ item teamfights where your range and splash beat her all-in","Punishing her W (Rocket Jump) cooldown after she commits","A frontline to absorb her jump so you kite from max range"],"foe":["A level 6 all-in with Buster Shot to burst and knock you away","First-item reset dives under your tower","Catching you in W range at low HP for a one-combo kill"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are even skill: Tristana has no poke and you have no early all-in, so it's a farm phase decided by wave control and whether you punish her Rocket Jump cooldown.","mid":"Level 6 and first item swing to Tristana because Buster Shot plus her E detonation and W reset give her a dive-and-burst all-in you can't yet out-trade; play safe and don't overstay in jump range.","late":"From 2+ items you take over: your Fishbones splash, superior range, and resets outscale her front-loaded all-in, so make her W commitment land into your frontline and kite her down.","whys":["Level 1 is even skill with neither champ holding an early lever.","Level 2 stays skill-based since Tristana lacks poke and you lack an all-in.","Level 3 remains even, decided by wave control and punishing her jump.","Levels 4-5 are still even skill as it's a farm phase before her ult comes online.","Level 6 is Tristana's: Buster Shot plus her detonation combo gives her a burst all-in you can't match.","First item stays Tristana's as her reset-fueled all-in and dive potential peak before your spike.","With 2+ items Jinx wins on superior range, Fishbones splash, and reset-driven late-game DPS."]},
  {"a":"jinx_bot","b":"twitch","win":["Jinx","Jinx","Skill","Skill","Twitch","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You start ahead but it levels off. Early, Twitch is a weak laner with short auto range and relies on his Q (Ambush) stealth for ganks and picks, so bully him levels 1-2 with Fishbones poke while he has no answer. By 3-5 it's even: he stacks Deadly Venom passively and can stealth-reposition, so watch for him vanishing and don't facecheck the brush at low HP."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Twitch-favoured. Spray and Pray (his R) turns his autos into piercing line damage that shreds a grouped 2v2, and combined with Contaminate (E) detonating his venom stacks he can burst you from stealth range at 6. Ward the flanks, keep your support between you and his likely Ambush angle, and don't group tightly where his R line hits you both."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Even/skill. Both of you spike on your first crit or attack-speed item, but Twitch's R plus stacked venom makes his teamfight burst genuinely rival yours, and his stealth lets him pick a fight on his terms. You out-DPS him in a fair, spaced fight, so the phase comes down to vision and who catches whom off-guard rather than a clean lane advantage."},{"when":"Late","text":"Skill/even and dangerous. Twitch is one of the few ADCs whose late-game teamfight output matches Jinx's: his R shreds your whole team through stealth flanks while your Fishbones and resets do the same to his. Prioritize vision to deny his Ambush flank, never walk alone, and win the fight by spotting his engage first and blowing him up before Spray and Pray gets rolling."}],"wants":{"you":["Levels 1-2 poke before Twitch stacks venom and R","Deep vision to deny his Ambush stealth flanks","A spaced, fair teamfight where your DPS beats his"],"foe":["A grouped 2v2 or 5v5 for Spray and Pray line damage","Stealth flanks from Ambush to catch you off-guard","Contaminate detonating full venom stacks to burst you"]},"early":"You win the opening levels 1-2 while Twitch is a weak, short-range laner, so poke him with Fishbones before he comes online.","mid":"Levels 3-5 even out as he stacks venom and gains stealth utility, then level 6 tilts to Twitch because Spray and Pray plus Contaminate lets him shred and burst you from a flank.","late":"From items on it's a knife's edge: Twitch's R matches your teamfight output, so win on vision and spacing, denying his Ambush and bursting him before his ult ramps.","whys":["Level 1 is Jinx's: Twitch is a weak short-range laner you can poke freely with Fishbones.","Level 2 stays yours as you keep punishing him before he stacks venom.","Level 3 evens out once he has stealth utility and passive venom online.","Levels 4-5 are even skill, decided by vision and whether he catches you from stealth.","Level 6 is Twitch's: Spray and Pray plus Contaminate gives him a flank-burst that outguns you when grouped.","First item is even skill since both spike and his R-fueled burst rivals your DPS.","With 2+ items it stays even: Twitch's late teamfight output matches Jinx's, so vision and spacing decide it."]},
  {"a":"jinx_bot","b":"varus","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Varus","Varus","Varus","Jinx"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Varus takes the edge here. His Q (Piercing Arrow) is a long-range charged poke that outranges your Pow-Pow autos, and W (Blighted Quiver) stacks let him melt you if he lands Q on a full-stacked target. Play behind minions so his Q clips creeps first, farm with Fishbones from max range, and don't stand in a straight line where his charged Q chunks you off CS."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Still Varus-favoured. Chain of Corruption (his R) is a spreading root that, with support follow-up, locks you down for a full W-stack burst combo, and it's a hard-engage tool you have no dash to escape. Hold Flash for his R, hug your frontline, and don't get caught in the open where his ult roots you into a kill."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Varus's window peaks here. His Q-max poke build plus first item lets him zone you off farm and burst you through his W stacks before your crit spike fully arrives. Concede some CS, freeze or hold the wave near your tower, and wait out this phase rather than contesting; your payoff comes one item later than his."},{"when":"Late","text":"You reclaim it at 2+ items. Varus is a lane-bully and mid-game poke threat but falls off relative to a fed Jinx: your Fishbones splash, uncapped Pow-Pow range, and Get Excited! resets make you the stronger sustained-DPS carry in grouped fights. Sit at max range behind your frontline, dodge his R, and out-scale him once your items come online."}],"wants":{"you":["Late 2+ item teamfights where resets and splash outscale him","Holding Flash to dodge Chain of Corruption","A frontline to absorb his poke and R while you kite"],"foe":["Straight-line angles to land charged Piercing Arrow poke","Level 6 R-into-W-stack burst with support follow-up","First-item poke build to zone you off farm before your spike"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are even skill, played around dodging his charged Q behind minions and farming safely with Fishbones.","mid":"Levels 4-6 and first item all favour Varus: his Q poke, W-stack burst, and Chain of Corruption root give him the kill pressure, so concede CS, hold Flash for his R, and wait out his spike.","late":"From 2+ items you overtake him, as Varus falls off while your splash, range, and resets make you the superior late carry; kite from max range and dodge his ult.","whys":["Level 1 is even skill with neither champ holding a decisive opening lever.","Level 2 stays even as both farm toward their power spikes.","Level 3 remains skill-based, decided by whether you dodge his charged Q behind minions.","Levels 4-5 are Varus's: his Q poke and W-stack burst zone you off farm.","Level 6 stays Varus's because Chain of Corruption roots you into a full burst combo.","First item is Varus's as his poke build peaks and zones you before your crit spike lands.","With 2+ items Jinx wins: Varus falls off while your splash, range, and resets scale into the better carry."]},
  {"a":"jinx_bot","b":"vayne","win":["Jinx","Jinx","Jinx","Jinx","Skill","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Your rocket-form Q outranges Vayne's 550 auto range hard, so shove the wave and poke her off CS with Zap! (W) every time she steps up to last-hit; she has no way to trade back before Tumble (Q) resets."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Both hit power spikes but yours is a global execute rocket while her Final Hour just gives stealth and Silver Bolt bonus damage; if she Ults to all-in, drop Flame Chompers (E) between you and her invisible reposition to root her out of stealth."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Vayne comes online here: with a first item and Final Hour her Silver Bolts three-shot you, so the lane evens out and your safety depends on spacing behind minions."},{"when":"Late","text":"In 5v5 Vayne is a monster if she reaches your backline through Tumble stealth, so play tight to your frontline, use E to zone her Condemn approach, and rely on your reset AS to out-DPS shared objectives."}],"wants":{"you":["Shove and poke her off farm before she has items","Land Zap! when she walks up to last-hit","Keep E ready to root her out of Tumble stealth"],"foe":["Survive laning to 1-2 items and Final Hour","Silver Bolt three-shot you in extended fights","Tumble-stealth around your frontline in teamfights"]},"early":"You own the first four levels flat out: rocket-form Q outranges her 550 autos, so shove hard and chunk her with Zap! whenever she steps to CS, and she has no range or sustain to answer.","mid":"Keep bullying through the mid-levels while your range advantage holds; save Flame Chompers for when her Tumble tries to reset a trade, and respect that her R at 6 gives real all-in threat with support CC.","late":"Once Vayne has an item and Final Hour the duel is skill-and-spacing: her Silver Bolts shred you if she sticks, so play behind minions and frontline, kite with reset MS, and never get isolated.","whys":["You outrange Vayne's autos in rocket form and win level 1 trades.","Zap! and the shove let you deny her CS with no answer at level 2.","At 3 your poke and wave control keep her permanently off farm.","Through 4-5 she still lacks the items to trade back into your range.","At 6 her Final Hour all-in matches your ult threat, evening the fight.","With one item and Final Hour her Silver Bolts even the duel on skill.","Late game it comes down to spacing and frontline discipline, not levels."]},
  {"a":"jinx_bot","b":"veigar","win":["Jinx","Jinx","Veigar","Skill","Veigar","Jinx","Jinx"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once Veigar has Event Horizon (E) and Baleful Strike (Q) stacked, he threatens to cage you and chunk you for a third of your bar; respect the E radius and only step up in rocket form when his stun is on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Veigar's Primordial Burst (R) scales with your missing health and can nearly one-shot you out of a cage, so at 6 you must position outside E range and hold Flame Chompers to punish his engage rather than dueling into his combo."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With your first item and Get Excited resets you outrange his cage and can shove the wave in, freezing him under tower where his mana runs dry and your Zap! pokes safely."},{"when":"Late","text":"In teamfights you sit at max minigun range behind your frontline; if you dodge or wait out Event Horizon, Veigar is a squishy immobile mage your reset AS deletes once his combo is down."}],"wants":{"you":["Win the first two levels before he gets E","Shove and freeze him out of mana","Dodge Event Horizon then punish his cooldowns"],"foe":["Land Event Horizon to cage you for the combo","Hit his R burst on your missing health at 6","Farm safely with Baleful Strike from range"]},"early":"You control levels 1-2 with superior auto range and wave push before Veigar has his cage online, so trade freely and deny his early Baleful Strike stacks.","mid":"The lane tips to Veigar at 3 and again at 6: his Event Horizon into Q and R can burst you from full, so stop face-checking his E radius, farm from rocket range, and keep Flame Chompers for his all-in.","late":"Your first item flips it back your way; with resets and range you shove him under tower, drain his mana, and in fights you simply respect one cage cooldown before unloading.","whys":["You out-trade Veigar at level 1 before his cage exists.","At 2 your range and push deny his early stacking with no answer.","At 3 Event Horizon plus Q lets him cage and chunk you first.","Through 4-5 it is even as you learn to dodge his E windows.","At 6 his Primordial Burst can one-shot you out of a stun.","Your first item and resets outrange his cage and starve his mana.","Late you delete an immobile mage once his combo is on cooldown."]},
  {"a":"jinx_bot","b":"xayah","win":["Xayah","Xayah","Xayah","Xayah","Xayah","Jinx","Jinx"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Xayah out-trades you every level of lane: her Double Daggers (Q) and Deadly Plumage (W) give her attack speed and burst that beat your minigun ramp, and she is safe because Bladecaller feathers deal huge damage from range while you have no dash."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Featherstorm (R) makes her untargetable and dodges your Zap!, your Flame Chompers, and even a landed ult, so you cannot reliably all-in her at 6; play for farm and avoid extended trades into her W window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is your turn: once you complete your first item your Get Excited resets and rocket range let you shove her in and poke, and your DPS ceiling in a sustained fight starts to eclipse hers."},{"when":"Late","text":"With two-plus items Jinx is the superior teamfighter; you sit at max range in rocket form, avoid her feather root line, and your uncapped attack speed and resets out-scale her lane-bully kit."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive the losing early lane and farm safely","Complete your first item to unlock resets","Out-DPS her from max range in extended fights"],"foe":["Snowball the early levels with W attack speed","Dodge your ult and CC with Featherstorm at 6","Root you with a Bladecaller feather line before you scale"]},"early":"Xayah wins the early lane hard: with Double Daggers and Deadly Plumage her attack speed and feather burst beat your minigun ramp, and you have no dash to escape, so concede the shove and farm safely at range.","mid":"Keep respecting her through 6 where Featherstorm dodges your Zap!, Chompers, and ult; do not force trades into her W, just soak XP, dodge feather roots, and wait for your item spike.","late":"Once your first item lands the matchup swings: your resets and rocket range let you shove her in and out-DPS her in any sustained fight, and at two-plus items you are the clearly stronger teamfighter.","whys":["Xayah's level 1 kit and feathers out-trade your slow minigun ramp.","At 2 her W attack speed and burst beat you with no escape for you.","At 3 her feather damage and safety keep you off the trade entirely.","Through 4-5 she still bullies the lane while you scale behind.","Her Featherstorm at 6 dodges your ult and CC, denying your all-in.","Your first item and resets flip the DPS race in your favour.","Late your range and uncapped attack speed out-scale her kit."]},
  {"a":"jinx_bot","b":"zeri","win":["Jinx","Jinx","Zeri","Skill","Zeri","Skill","Jinx"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Zeri spikes at 3 once she has her Q auto-attacks and Ultrashock Laser (W); her poke and wall-dash mobility let her hit-and-run you, and your minigun can't stick to her, so shove and poke with Zap! rather than chasing."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"At 6 Zeri's Lightning Crash (R) turns her into a hyper-mobile skirmisher who dashes through your Flame Chompers and kites your rockets; don't all-in into her ult, and hold E to zone her dash path if your support engages."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Roughly even at first item: she stays slippery but your rocket range and Get Excited resets let you match her waveclear and punish her if she over-extends past minions."},{"when":"Late","text":"With two-plus items your teamfight ceiling wins; sit at max range, use E to cut her dash-chain approach, and your uncapped attack speed out-DPSes her once you are peeled from her hit-and-run kiting."}],"wants":{"you":["Win the first two levels before her Q comes online","Shove and poke rather than chase her mobility","Out-scale her with range and resets at two items"],"foe":["Spike at 3 with Q autos and W poke","Kite you endlessly with Lightning Crash mobility","Hit-and-run your slow minigun through walls"]},"early":"You take the first two levels: before Zeri's Q attacks ramp she is a weak lane-two, so trade with autos and Zap! and deny her the early tempo she needs.","mid":"Zeri owns 3 and 6 with her poke and Lightning Crash mobility, dashing through Chompers and kiting your rockets, so stop chasing, shove waves, and only commit when your support locks her down.","late":"By two-plus items your range and resets flip it back; cut her dash approach with Flame Chompers, hold max distance, and out-DPS her once she can't hit-and-run you freely.","whys":["You out-trade Zeri at level 1 before her Q ramps up.","At 2 your auto range and Zap! keep her off tempo.","At 3 her Q autos and W poke give her the kiting edge.","Through 4-5 it is even as you trade shove for her mobility.","Her Lightning Crash at 6 lets her dash your CC and kite your rockets.","At first item you match her waveclear and even the skirmish.","Late your range and resets out-scale her hit-and-run kit."]},
  {"a":"jinx_bot","b":"ziggs","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Ziggs","Ziggs","Jinx","Jinx"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ziggs shifts ahead here: Bouncing Bomb (Q) out-pokes your auto range and pushes the wave into your tower, forcing you to farm under turret while he chips you; last-hit with rocket-form Q and dodge his bombs by moving between minions."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His Mega Inferno Bomb (R) adds long-range execute and objective pressure, so at 6 you can't safely step up to CS during his cooldowns; respect his poke wave, hold Flame Chompers for a support engage, and don't get chunked before fights."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You come online: with your first item, Get Excited resets and rocket range you can match his shove, poke back at distance, and threaten an all-in if he oversteps his Satchel Charge (W) escape."},{"when":"Late","text":"In 5v5 you out-scale him as a carry; stay spread to avoid his AoE bomb poke, sit at max range, and your sustained DPS and resets far exceed his single-target teamfight threat."}],"wants":{"you":["Farm safely under tower through his early poke","Reach your first item to match his shove","Out-scale him as a sustained-DPS carry"],"foe":["Poke you off CS with Bouncing Bomb","Perma-shove the wave into your tower","Zone and execute with Mega Inferno Bomb"]},"early":"The first levels are an even skill lane: Ziggs pokes with Q but you can shove back and trade autos, so it comes down to who dodges bombs and controls the wave better.","mid":"Ziggs edges ahead at 4-6 as his Bouncing Bomb poke and R pressure push you under tower; farm safely with rocket-form Q, weave between minions to dodge, and save E for his engage.","late":"Your first item flips the lane and the scaling: resets and rocket range let you match his shove and out-range his poke, and as a late-game carry your DPS dwarfs his single-target teamfight output.","whys":["Level 1 is even; it hinges on dodging his first Bouncing Bomb.","At 2 you can still shove and trade autos into his poke.","Through 3 it stays a skill lane of wave control and bomb dodging.","At 4 his Q poke and perma-shove pin you under tower.","His Mega Inferno Bomb at 6 zones and executes you from range.","Your first item and resets let you match his shove and poke back.","Late your sustained carry DPS out-scales his single-target bombs."]}
